# Fashion-MNIST Image Classification Using Neural Networks

## Author
Gael Liale-Fezeu

Course: Learning Plan 12 – Neural Networks and Deep Learning Basics

## Data Preprocessing

The following preprocessing steps were applied:

### Image Normalization
- Pixel values scaled from 0–255 to 0–1

### Image Flattening
- Converted 28×28 images into 784-feature vectors

### Data Visualization
- Sample images displayed to understand dataset categories

## Neural Network Architecture

### Input Layer
- 784 Features

### Hidden Layer 1
- 128 Neurons
- ReLU Activation

### Hidden Layer 2
- 64 Neurons
- ReLU Activation

### Output Layer
- 10 Neurons
- Softmax Activation

### Optimizer
- Adam

### Loss Function
- Sparse Categorical Crossentropy

### Metric
- Accuracy

## Training Configuration

- Epochs: 15
- Batch Size: 64
- Validation Split: 20%

## Results

### Model Performance
- Test Accuracy ≈ 88%

### Best Performing Classes
- Trouser
- Sandal
- Bag
- Ankle Boot

### More Challenging Classes
- Shirt
- Pullover
- Coat

The confusion matrix showed that visually similar clothing types were more likely to be misclassified.

## Model Improvements

Experiments included:

### Larger Hidden Layers
- 128 → 256 neurons
- 64 → 128 neurons

### Data Augmentation
- Rotation
- Zoom
- Width Shifting
- Height Shifting

These modifications increased model learning capacity and robustness.

